#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:3
msgid "Pyodide Deprecation Timeline"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:5
msgid ""
"Each Pyodide release may deprecate certain features from previous releases "
"in a backward incompatible way. If a feature is deprecated, it will continue "
"to work until its removal, but raise warnings. We try to ensure deprecations "
"are done over at least two minor(feature) releases, however, as Pyodide is "
"still in beta state, this list is subject to change and some features can be "
"removed without deprecation warnings. More details about each item can often "
"be found in the {ref}`changelog`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:13
msgid "314.1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:15
msgid ""
"`jsproxy.as_object_map()` will be removed. Use `jsproxy.as_py_json()` "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:17
msgid "0.25.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:19
msgid ""
"Typescript type imports for `PyProxy` subtypes from `pyodide` will be "
"removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:21
msgid ""
"The methods `PyProxy.supportsHas`, `PyProxy.isCallable`, etc will be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:23
msgid ""
"Support for the `homedir` argument will be removed in favor of `env: {HOME: "
"\"/the/home/directory\"}`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:26
msgid "0.24.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:28
msgid ""
"The `messageCallback` and `errorCallback` argument to `loadPackage` and "
"`loadPackagesFromImports` will be passed as a named argument only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:31
msgid "`Py2JsResult` will be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:33
msgid "The `--output-directory` argument to `pyodide build` will be removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:35
msgid "0.23.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:37
msgid ""
"Names that used to be in the root `pyodide` module and were moved to "
"submodules will no longer be available in the root module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:39
msgid ""
"The \"message\" argument to `PyProxy.destroy` method will no longer be "
"accepted as a positional argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:42
msgid "0.21.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:44
msgid ""
"The `globals` argument to `runPython` and `runPythonAsync` will be passed as "
"a named argument only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:46
msgid ""
"The `extractDir` argument to `unpackArchive` will be passed as a named "
"argument only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:49
msgid "0.20.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:51
msgid ""
"The skip-host key will be removed from the meta.yaml format. If needed, "
"install a host copy of the package with pip instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:53
msgid ""
"`pyodide-interrupts` module will be removed. If you were using this for some "
"reason, use {js:func}`~pyodide.setInterruptBuffer` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:56
msgid "0.19.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:58
msgid ""
"The default working directory (home directory) inside the Pyodide virtual "
"file system has been changed from `/` to `/home/pyodide`. To get the "
"previous behavior, you can"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:61
msgid "call `os.chdir(\"/\")` in Python to change working directory or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:62
msgid "call {js:func}`~exports.loadPyodide` with the `homedir=\"/\"` argument"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/deprecation-timeline.md:65
msgid ""
"When a JavaScript function is called from Python, PyProxy arguments and "
"return values will be automatically destroyed when the function is finished."
msgstr ""
